(3.3 Viewing Billing History) Tj
T*
(Your full billing history, including all subscription charges and receipts, is) Tj
T*
(available in Account > Billing History. You can download individual receipts as PDFs) Tj
T*
(for expense reporting.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(=============================================================) Tj
T*
(4. PLAN CHANGES \(UPGRADES AND DOWNGRADES\)) Tj
T*
(=============================================================) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4.1 Upgrading Your Plan) Tj
T*
(You can upgrade from Basic to Premium or Family at any time. The price difference for) Tj
T*
(the remaining days in your current billing cycle is calculated on a prorated basis) Tj
T*
(and charged immediately. Your new plan benefits activate immediately.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Example: If you are on Basic \($9.99/month\) and upgrade to Premium \($19.99/month\) with) Tj
T*
(15 days remaining in your cycle, you will be charged approximately $5.00 immediately) Tj
T*
(\(half the $10 monthly difference\). Your next full renewal will be at the Premium) Tj
T*
(rate.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4.2 Downgrading Your Plan) Tj
T*
(You can downgrade your plan at any time. The downgrade takes effect at the end of) Tj
T*
(your current billing period ? you continue to enjoy your current plan's benefits) Tj
T*
(until then. No refund is issued for the remaining days of the higher-tier plan.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4.3 Switching Between Monthly and Annual Billing) Tj
T*
(Switching from monthly to annual billing can be done at any time. You will be charged) Tj
T*
(the annual rate immediately, and your billing cycle resets to the date of the switch.) Tj
T*
(If you switch from annual to monthly, the change takes effect at the end of your) Tj
T*
(current annual period.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(=============================================================) Tj
T*
(5. PAUSING YOUR SUBSCRIPTION) Tj
T*
(=============================================================) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.1 Pause Eligibility) Tj
T*
(Subscription pausing is available for accounts that have been active for at least 60) Tj
T*
(days. You may pause your subscription for a minimum of 1 month and a maximum of 3) Tj
T*
(consecutive months.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.2 How to Pause) Tj
T*
(Go to Account > Subscriptions > Pause Subscription. Select the number of months to) Tj
T*
(pause \(1, 2, or 3\). Your subscription and billing are suspended immediately. Benefits) Tj
T*
(are deactivated during the pause period. At the end of the pause, your subscription) Tj
T*
(resumes and billing restarts automatically on the same schedule.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.3 Pause Limits) Tj
T*
(You may pause your subscription a maximum of once per 12-month period. Pausing a) Tj
T*
(subscription does not affect your account history, order history, or accumulated) Tj
T*
(store credit.) Tj
